---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Komal and Tivra Swaras | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Unlock the black keys — flat and sharp notes that give Indian ragas their distinct character. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Komal and Tivra Swaras</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-beginner capitalize">beginner</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 20 min · Lesson 5 of 8</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Komal and Tivra Swaras</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Unlock the black keys — flat and sharp notes that give Indian ragas their distinct character.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Komal = flattened swara (black key to the left)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Tivra = sharpened swara (black key to the right)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Four swaras can be komal: Re Ga Dha Ni</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Only one swara can be tivra: Ma</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Sa and Pa are achala — never komal or tivra</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>Why Komal and Tivra Exist</h2>
      <p>The 7 natural swaras form a basic major scale. But Indian music uses up to 12 distinct pitches in an octave — the same 12 as Western music. The additional 5 come from komal (flattened) and tivra (sharpened) versions of certain swaras. These altered swaras are the building blocks of ragas and what gives each raga its unique emotional color.</p>

      <h2>The Four Komal Swaras</h2>
      <p>Komal Re equals C sharp (black key W after Sa). Komal Ga equals D sharp (black key E). Komal Dha equals G sharp (black key Y). Komal Ni equals A sharp (black key U). On the keyboard each komal swara is the black key immediately LEFT of the natural swara. In notation komal swaras are shown with a subscript dot or lowercase letter.</p>

      <h2>Tivra Ma</h2>
      <p>Only Madhyama (Ma) has a tivra (sharp) version: Tivra Ma equals F sharp (T key on our harmonium). Tivra Ma is the black key between natural Ma (F) and Pa (G). It is famous as the defining characteristic of Raga Yaman — in fact using Tivra Ma instead of natural Ma is the one thing that instantly identifies Yaman.</p>

      <h2>Achala Swaras — The Fixed Notes</h2>
      <p>Sa (Shadja) and Pa (Pancham) are achala swaras meaning fixed or immovable. They appear in virtually every raga and never become komal or tivra. This is why there are no black keys between E and F (Ga and Ma) and between B and C (Ni and Sa). These gaps are not mistakes — they reflect the special nature of Sa and Pa.</p>

      <h2>Chromatic Scale Practice</h2>
      <p>Now practice all 12 notes: C C# D D# E F F# G G# A A# B in sequence. Keys on our web harmonium: A W S E D F T G Y H U J. This chromatic scale covers every possible note. Practicing it builds complete keyboard familiarity and prepares you to play in any raga. Do it ascending and descending 5 times daily.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>